Japan Government ‘Cautiously Optimistic’ on Economy, Sumi Says

-- B y   S h a m i m   A d a m
-- 
2011-09-15T01:25:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/japan-government-cautiously-optimistic-on-economy-sumi-says.html
Japan ’s government is “cautiously
optimistic” about the outlook for the nation’s economy,
Chikahisa Sumi, deputy director general of  government finance  at
Japan’s Ministry of Finance, said in a speech in  Singapore 
today. Japan can’t “blindly” proceed with fiscal
consolidation, he also said.   To contact the reporter on this story:
